South Africa‘s Truworths International reported on Thursday a 2% rise in retail sales for the first 18 trading weeks of its 2020 financial year despite difficult conditions. The South African-listed clothing, shoes, jewellery and homeware retailer said sales rose to R6.3 billion during the period from July 1 to November 3, with an increase in sales from its African business. ($1 = 14.7611)